  "text": "Our study analyzed the effects of HAART regimens, but not individual drugs because of sample size issues. Nonetheless, we were aware that different antiretroviral drugs even in the same class might carry differential degrees of toxicity on cerebral small vessels. This matter in question can be addressed in future studies using experimental animals [CITATION_1] and in-vitro cell systems [CITATION_2] . Also, the toxic effects of antiretroviral drugs might vary with the duration of drug use and drug metabolism. We found the estimated total duration of exposure to any antiretroviral regimens in the entire follow-up period was not significantly associated with either mild or moderate/ severe CSVD. Unfortunately, available data on the duration of each antiretroviral regimen used were not sufficient for analysis.",
